A '''captive power plant''' also called '''autoproducer''' or '''embedded generation''' is a [[Electricity generation|power generation]] facility used and managed by an industrial or commercial energy user for their own energy consumption. Captive power plants can operate [[Off-the-grid|off-grid]] or they can be connected to the electric grid to exchange excess generation.<ref>{{cite web|title=Captive power plant|url=https://www.clarke-energy.com/captive-power-plants/|website=www.clarke-energy.com|publisher=Clarke Energy|accessdate=5 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Captive power generation {{!}} Norton Rose Fulbright - What is a captive power plant?|url=http://www.insideafricalaw.com/publications/captive-power-generation|website=www.insideafricalaw.com|accessdate=5 September 2016}}</ref>
Captive power plants are generally used by power-intensive industries where continuity and quality of energy supply are crucial, such as [[aluminum smelter]]s, [[steel production|steel plants]], [[Chemical industry|chemical industries]] etc.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Mohanta|first1=Dusmanta Kumar|last2=Sadhu|first2=Pradip Kumar|last3=Chakrabarti|first3=R.|title=Deterministic and stochastic approach for safety and reliability optimization of captive power plant maintenance scheduling using GA/SA-based hybrid techniques: A comparison of results|journal=Reliability Engineering & System Safety|date=February 2007|volume=92|issue=2|pages=187–199|doi=10.1016/j.ress.2005.11.062}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Distributed generation]] *[[Prosumer#Producer_and_consumer|Prosumer]]
