In [[chemistry]], '''pentagonal pyramidal molecular geometry''' describes the shape of compounds where in six atoms or groups of atoms  or [[ligand]]s are arranged around a central atom, defining the vertices of a [[pentagonal pyramid]]. It is one of the few [[Molecular geometry|molecular geometries]] with uneven [[bond angle]]s.  

[[Image:AX6E1-2D.png|thumb|left|100px|AX<sub>6</sub>E<sub>1</sub>]]

